title: Man dies after 5-story fall in Oshkosh
content:
A 20-year-old man is dead after falling five stories from an Oshkosh building. 
 
Officers say it appears to be a workplace accident. 
 
Police say the man fell from a building on the 600-block of Hazel Street at 12:40 Wednesday afternoon. He died at the hospital from his injuries. 
 
Police didn’t say what work the man was doing on the building. 
 
The Occupational Safety and Health Administration and the Winnebago Coroner’s office are investigating, along with the police department. 
 
Police aren’t releasing the man’s name yet so his family can be notified.
